# Smash That Like Button

Content creators on YouTube keep asking. Now you can fulfill their wishes with this bookmarklet.

## How It Works

- Open a YouTube video
- Click the bookmark

## Installation

A bookmark normally loads a web page. A bookmarklet is a bookmark that runs javascript on the current page instead of taking you to a new URL. Bookmarklets use an [IIFE](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/IIFE) (Immediately Invoked Function Expression).

```
javascript:(function(){ //Do Stuff... })();
```

**To install this bookmarklet:**

- Create a new **bookmark** (to anywhere)
- Edit the bookmark and replace the address with:

```
javascript:(function(){let target = document.querySelectorAll('#menu ytd-toggle-button-renderer')[0];
let rect = target.getBoundingClientRect();
let rotation = parseInt(Math.random() * 20);
let glassSize = 300;
let magicX = Math.random() * (rect.right - rect.left) + rect.left;
let magicY = Math.random() * (rect.bottom - rect.top) + rect.top;
let crackX = magicX - (0.5*glassSize);
let crackY = magicY - (0.5*glassSize);
let crack = document.createElement('img');
crack.src = 'data:image/png;base64,';
crack.style = `display:block;width:${glassSize}px;height:${glassSize}px;transform:rotate(${rotation}deg);position:absolute;opacity:0.9;mix-blend-mode:hard-light;top:${crackY}px;left:${crackX}px;`;
document.querySelector('body').appendChild(crack);
target.click();
})();
```
